analysis: The agent used an incorrect datetime format for the end time in the MediaDesignOptimizer_createVisualContent call ("2022-04-15T23:59:59Z" instead of the expected "2022-04-15T00:00:00"), resulting in a parameter mismatch and failure to match the expected function call.

The agent only made two function calls—one per model/period combination—when it should have made four calls covering all combinations of model type (Random Forest, Neural Network) and forecast period (1 month, 3 months). It failed to fully enumerate the required parameter pairs.

The agent set the licenseManager calls' timeFrame to a single day ("2025-10-09" to "2025-10-09") instead of using the full year ("2025-01-01" to "2025-12-31") as specified, causing a parameter mismatch with the expected function calls.

The agent output multiple tool calls as consecutive <tool_call> blocks within a single response, instead of as a parsable JSON array or valid combined structure, causing parsing failure due to invalid format and trailing characters.

The model output function calls used "arguments" instead of the expected "parameters" key in the JSON structure, causing the evaluator to not recognize the calls despite the correct content. The essential issue is a schema mismatch in function call formatting.

The agent made two key errors: it set the writing prompt complexity to "detailed" instead of matching the specified "advanced" level, and it placed "analysis_depth" at the wrong JSON hierarchy for the shape comparison, resulting in malformed function call arguments.

The agent incorrectly added specific technology feature filters ("technologyFeatures") to the function calls instead of only specifying the required releaseTime parameters, resulting in no matching function calls and failure to retrieve the general technology information as requested.

The agent used the wrong timePeriod parameters when calling CinemaPhilosophyAnalyzer_analyzeSocietalThemes for "Inception"—it incorrectly set the analysis range to 2011-2020 instead of focusing on the film's actual release year, 2010.

The agent incorrectly included the "severity" field in the "weather_conditions" arguments, which is not accepted by the function schema; only "condition_type" should be provided, leading to a mismatch with the expected function calls.

The agent's JSON for the document_management_store tool call was malformed due to a missing closing brace, resulting in a parsing error and failure to execute the action despite having otherwise correct parameters and logic.

The agent erroneously included actual feedback data in the MarketingCampaign_manageFeedback call instead of leaving the feedbackData arrays empty as requested, thus not matching the expected input structure for generating a feedback report.
The agent omitted the required "intensity": "High" field in the checkParameters for each function call, resulting in incomplete parameter sets that did not match the expected function input schema.

The agent used a hardcoded current date of "2026-11-01" as the range start for the cybersecurity threat evaluation, instead of the required "2026-01-01" (beginning of the year), resulting in an incorrect date range for the function call.

The agent used "United States" instead of the required "USA" in the country field for the urban_air_quality_monitor function, causing a mismatch with the expected function call parameters. This led to the evaluator not recognizing the function call as correct.

The agent incorrectly specified "cardboard boxes" instead of "cardboard" as the packaging material in the FruitSorter_processSortedFruits call, causing a parameter mismatch and resulting in no match with the expected function call.

The agent incorrectly included unnecessary "document_id" fields in the insurance_claim_verification function call, deviating from the expected parameter structure. This mismatch caused the evaluator not to recognize the function call as valid, resulting in the failure.

The agent incorrectly included the "interactions" field in the function call "details" argument, which was not present in the expected parameters. This extra field caused an argument mismatch, leading to no matching function call being recognized by the evaluator.

The agent supplied an incorrect severity value (5 instead of the expected 3) for the "swelling" symptom in the ReptileBiteResponseSystem_evaluateBiteSeverity call, resulting in a parameter mismatch and no matching function call.

The agent omitted the required "themes": ["Existentialism"] parameter in the PhilosophyCinemaExplorer_findPurposeDrivenFilms call, failing to filter for existential themes as the user requested, which led to a mismatch with the expected function call.

The agent's call to VisaInformationManager_getVisaRequirements omitted the required "documentTypes" parameter ("passport"), resulting in a function call that did not match the expected signature. This omission led to the failure.
The agent omitted the required "event_details" field in its function call arguments, resulting in a schema mismatch with the expected input structure for the historical_migration_timeline function.

The agent incorrectly grouped all vehicles into a single function call and omitted the required infrastructureResponse details for each, instead of making four separate, fully specified function calls with individual vehicle data and corresponding infrastructure responses as expected.

The agent incorrectly included "terms" parameters ("Deposit" and "Closing Costs") in both RealEstateBiddingAssistant_startNegotiation calls, which are not part of the function's expected parameters, causing the evaluator to reject the calls as non-matching.

The agent included an unsupported "terms" parameter in the RealEstateBiddingAssistant_startNegotiation call and omitted the required "date" parameter in the RealEstateAdvisor_getMortgageDetails call, resulting in function signatures that did not match the expected tool interface.

The agent failed to specify unique identifiers for the resistors in the second circuit and incorrectly described the connection as "from: resistor, to: resistor" instead of identifying them as "resistor1" and "resistor2" to clarify the parallel connection, resulting in a function call mismatch.

The agent incorrectly included the "operationHours" parameter in the RefrigeratorOptimizer_optimizeEnergyUsage function call, which was not part of the expected parameters, resulting in a mismatch and failure to match the required function signature.

The agent failed to correctly capitalize "description" as "Turf maintenance" in the football_venue_management call, producing "turf maintenance" instead. This minor mismatch led to the evaluator not recognizing the function call as matching the expected output.

The agent incorrectly included an empty "contact_number" field in the applicant_details for each function call, which was not present in the expected parameters. This mismatch prevented the function calls from matching the expected schema.

The agent incorrectly set the "intensity" parameter to 0.9 instead of the expected value of 1 and unnecessarily included "apply_time": "real-time" in the audio_effect_processor function call, resulting in a non-matching function signature.

The agent incorrectly set the "timeOfDay" parameter as "night" for AudioConfigurator_optimizeSound and omitted the "timeOfDay" parameter for DiskTemperatureControl_adjustCoolingSystem, both of which were required and specified in the expected function calls.

The agent incorrectly formatted the "settings" parameter for HomeLightingControl_manageLightSettings as a list instead of a single object, causing a mismatch with the expected function argument structure and failure to match the required call.
The agent incorrectly formatted the "details" field as an object instead of as a list of scenario objects, resulting in a mismatch with the expected function call parameters structure.
The agent incorrectly combined multiple countries into a single function call instead of making separate calls for each country as required, resulting in a mismatch in the number of function calls.

The agent omitted the required "includeEvents": false parameter for the Colosseum call, causing its function arguments not to match the expected signature and leading to failure in function call matching.

The agent used "property division" (lowercase) instead of "Property division" (title case) in the "disputeNature" parameter for the InheritanceMediationScheduler_scheduleSession call, causing an exact match failure with the expected function parameters.
